description.narrative: The External communication, advocacy and partnership unit successfully engaged the general public, donors and the media, and brought more visibility to the situation of children affected by the humanitarian crisis in Burkina Faso. Increased media outreach resulted in positive coverage in media including more than 50 articles and TV and radio reports, and placement in international media. The office leveraged local artists to produced music, including in local languages, which promoted protective measures against COVID-19. Other multimedia and animated products were also disseminated as part of the outreach campaigns to educate the public about the COVID-19 pandemic. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/01/2022
